    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="921"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d921">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./9–344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-03T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 3, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 3—4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3461. My 3389, August 30, 7 p.m. Boheman has informed me that all Mr. Gunther
                    said to me on August 30 is now officially confirmed. The Minister of the
                    Interior will make the formal announcement in a speech which may be forthcoming
                    at any moment.<note n="22" xml:id="d921fn22">Formal announcement made on
                        September 5.</note>
                </p>
                <p>He will declare in words to this effect: That Sweden will not give asylum to war
                    refugees of any category who have been guilty of acts or crimes which are an
                    affront to the conscience of humanity.</p>
                <p>The Ministers of Interior and Justice are collaborating in drawing up directives
                    and instructions to implement this decision, which will be given to the police,
                    customs, immigration, army, navy, frontier guards and all authorities whose duty
                    it will be to enforce the policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
